Don't think about evading the taxman. That's the word from Sars Commissioner Edward Kieswetter, who says tax fraudsters will be dealt with. He was speaking at a media briefing in Pretoria on the first day of the new tax season. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Tax Season is officially underway. Sars Commissioner Edward Kieswetter has warned that tax fraudsters will be dealt with. He was speaking at a media briefing in Pretoria on the first day of the new tax season on Monday. READ: Tax season kicks off “We see examples of fictitious refunds that are claimed by fabricating expenses and losses. We see fictitious employers who are created to generate IRP5s.” We would like to issue a very strong caution to those who believe that they can get away. To tell you that we working hard to detect that compliance and to enforce the law," Kieswetter said. Sars has set itself an ambitious revenue target of collecting more than R1,4-trillion for 2019/2020 tax year.